reviews.text:
23Feb19: the hygiene was improved and food quality resume normal. 

16Dec18: came again, but they charged wrong amount ($389 became $398) by credit card. Also, their is not that clean compare with few months ago. 

A nice restaurant with udon, chazuke, desserts, ice cream … tea set is cheap and delicious, no high chair provided, but the height of tables are fit for aged 3-4, must come again.

Lack of man power, only 1 server during the tea time. She was sooooo busy and we needed to wait for long.  Seat is too open wirhout any partition.  People from outside could see the diner in the restaurant clearly.  We felt so uncomfortable to be watched while we were dining.

Protion is another big issue, the afternoon set is too small, obviously it is overpriced.   I think I will dine in Watami again from now on.  At least, the portion, taste and the dining atmosphere is much better.

Follow my culinary journey on insta @luna_vona

During a casual stroll around V City shopping mall, we were attracted by the lovely, cozy interior of Gozen Cha.

The restaurants serves savoury as well as an impressive variety of sweet Japanese specialties. 

The two of us shared a signature desert platter, consisting a combination of their best-selling desserts. 

We were very pleasantly surprised with the stunning presentation of our order and the taste did not disappoint either. The ice cream was very aromatic and creamy, while the other ingredients together formed a lovely combination of texture and flavours.

However, at 78HKD,  it’s in my opinion slightly overpriced. 

The service was efficient and quick.
Ice cream not bad
Nice presentation

reviews.text: Literally this made living in Tuen Mun better because of the easy air conditioned stop right at the end of the line... great place to kill time but for the love of heaven I wish there were more benches here to just sit... mission accomplished, Tuen Mun, I'm forced to wander and not abuse the free air conditioning

The location is very convenience where you can reach with MTR, buses, light rail, minibuses and cross border coaches. You can go to T-park with the coach.
There are different types of food you can choose but the price is relatively high. The shopping center is not large.
Nice place. For most important clean toilets, because it says a lot about the place. And I can tell you, it was super clean.

A typical shopping mall in hong kong targets mainland chinese, not a good place for locals or tourists who want some different from other malls. No rest place and super crowded, especially in weekends.
there is a Samsung Electronic company here with good service
